&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 6 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a team of health care assistants to be employed on a Fixed term basis to offer sensitive care on a one to one basis to patients in their own homes. The post would involve all aspects of personal care for high dependent patients living with long term conditions. There is an expectation that the candidates have the relevant experience of working with high dependent patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours will be required to cover day and night duties on a rotational basis seven days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Emma Roberts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Case manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: emma.roberts240797@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
